This paper is about learning feedforward neural networks using randomized methods. The primary focus is on adjusting the random parameters to obtain a good projection space for approximating strongly nonlinear functions. This falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of activation functions and their impact on the performance of the network, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks for image processing, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the proposed method involves selecting input space regions and adjusting sigmoid slopes, which is related to signal processing (cs.SI).
